The paper discusses the security and privacy implications of browser fingerprinting, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). However, it also touches upon topics such as human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM) as it discusses the use of browser fingerprinting in online advertising and tracking. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for defense solutions and the challenges in implementing them, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and systems and information theory (cs.SI).
